Code of conduct – expectation of employees to follow guidelines on how to behave 

A code of conduct is how you conduct yourself. A code of practice is how you practice your craft.  

 

Code of practice – usually includes a code of conduct. Usually brings in legislation to relevant guidelines.  

 

Quality of work – meeting deadlines, not misrepresenting the work, client confidentiality, reliability. 

 

Contribution of society – promoting access to digital work, the work having a positive impact on society 

 

Safety – considering the consequences of their work 

 

Security and privacy – legally, personal data must be protected, 

 

Innovation – who owns what someone has made/ invented.  
